KATSINA – Governor Aminu Bello Masari of Katsina State has urged Nigerians to expect better things coming their way in 2022, saying that the new year is pregnant with endless positive possibilities. The Governor made the declaration in a statement signed by his DG Media Abdu Labaran Masari and made available to newsmen in Katsina on Saturday. While expressing optimism for better prospects for Nigerians in 2022, Masari said given the fact that 2022 would be the last full year President Buhari and some state governors will be calling the shots as helmsmen, there will be a more purposeful action in government’s efforts at the two tiers to make Nigeria less stressful for compatriots. Masari Signs 2022 Appropriation Bill Into Law Masari Urges POWA To Assist Police Officers’ Widows,… Specifically, he assured that the fight against insecurity would witness a more determined approach which will leave no room for the criminals’ breath. The Governor, who lamented the challenges posed by Covid 19 and banditry, promised that his administration would pull out all the stops to ensure that the year 2022 sign posts the total end of banditry in the state. “The expectations of the citizens will be substantially met, especially in the area of security”. He however, called for more support and cooperation with the government, especially at the centre to enable it record more successes in the new year.